{"id":16276,"date":"2023-10-05T04:05:53","date_gmt":"2023-10-05T04:05:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/?page_id=16276"},"modified":"2023-10-06T23:45:54","modified_gmt":"2023-10-06T23:45:54","slug":"attention-deficit-hyperactivity-disorder-adhd","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/attention-deficit-hyperactivity-disorder-adhd\/","title":{"rendered":"Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD)"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content_no_spaces&#8221; equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696478883146{margin-top: -50px !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696478907611{background-color: #00b3e6 !important;}&#8221;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696524715119{padding-top: 100px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 25px;\"><strong>Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD)<br \/>\n<\/strong><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 17px;\">ADHD is a common neurodevelopmental disorder characterized by impulsivity, hyperactivity, and difficulty sustaining attention. It is often diagnosed in childhood and can persist into adulthood, with symptoms varying among individuals.<\/span><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<div class=\"notranslate side-menu is-hidden is-left -center has-shadow\" id=\"side-menu-3\"><ul class=\"sm-list\"><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/benefits-of-aba-therapy\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Benefits-of-ABA.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Benefits of ABA Therapy<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/autism-101\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Autism-101.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Autism 101<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/developmental-disorders\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Development-Disorders.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Development Disorders<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/parent-family-coaching\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Parent-Family-Coaching.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Parent &amp; Family Coaching<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/development-milestones\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Steps.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Development Milestones<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/aba-assessment\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Assessment.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">ABA Assessment<\/span><\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/div>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696478875888{background-image: url(https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/ADHD-Girl.png?id=13078) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; gap=&#8221;20&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696481703602{padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696482552050{padding-right: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Though it may be normal for children to have trouble focusing and controlling impulsive behaviors (may act without thinking) or be overly active at one time or another, children with ADHD do not just grow out of these behaviors. Their symptoms continue, grow more severe, and cause difficulties at school, at home, or among friends.<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-14990 alignright lazyloaded\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 259px) 100vw, 259px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105.png 360w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105-120x120.png 120w\" alt=\"\" width=\"259\" height=\"259\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105.png 360w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105-120x120.png 120w\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/nino-tableta-libro_7710-105.png\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 259px) 100vw, 259px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">A child with ADHD might:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Daydream a lot<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Forget or lose things a lot<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Squirm or fidget<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Talk too much\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Make careless mistakes or take unnecessary risks<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Have a hard time resisting temptation<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Have trouble taking turns<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Have difficulty getting along with others<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">ADHD can range from mild to severe, depending on physiology and environment. <strong>This can affect school, work, and social situations.<\/strong>\u00a0In fact, many young children enter school with behavioral and cognitive symptoms that put them at a significant disadvantage compared with their typically-developing peers.<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">About 5 in 10 children with ADHD had a behavior or conduct problem.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">About 3 in 10 children with ADHD had anxiety.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696635278193{padding-right: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<\/p>\n<div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element vc_custom_1693701831659\">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px;\">Here are some of the symptoms and challenges that people with ADHD and autism often share:<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Impulsivity: Including speaking out of turn and jumping up when it\u2019s inappropriate<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Lack of focus: In ADHD, typically being distracted by external events, and in autism, being distracted by your own thoughts and ideas<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Problems with\u00a0executive functioning: Difficulties in the ability to organize time, tasks, and projects<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Challenges with social interaction and making friends<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Learning differences and disabilities<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Sensory challenges: Over- or under-responsiveness to light, sound, touch<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Emotional immaturity: Difficulty in managing anger and frustration<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696479135240{padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element vc_custom_1693701831659\">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040;\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 25px;\">The Difference Between Autism and ADHD<\/span><br \/>\n<\/span><\/b><\/span><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) and autism are both <em>neurodevelopmental<\/em> disorders, and they have several symptoms in common. For example, people with autism and ADHD may both be impulsive, and people with both disorders may develop speech later than is typical in children.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #f3781e; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\"><strong>While the symptoms of ADHD and autism may not look the same on paper, they can look very similar in person.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Traits like distractibility and impulsivity, for example, are part of the ADHD diagnosis. While they\u2019re not part of the autism diagnosis, they appear in most people with autism. Speech delays and idiosyncrasies are part of the autism spectrum disorder (ASD) diagnosis and not the ADHD diagnosis. Yet, people with ADHD often have speech delays.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner gap=&#8221;15&#8243;][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696482190984{margin-left: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #404040;\">ASD affects a person\u2019s social communication and interaction in various contexts. There is no cure, but support can help people make progress in the areas that they find challenging.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #404040;\">Children with ASD have a limited scope of interest; however, they may also have high levels of focus on favored topics. They may seem to obsess over things that they enjoy (may be able to recall facts and details easily) but have difficulty focusing on things they don\u2019t.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">ADHD, on the other hand, is a prevalent condition that can affect concentration, impulse control, and cognitive processes like planning before acting.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696482178107{padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<\/p>\n<div class=\"flex flex-grow flex-col gap-3 max-w-full\">\n<div class=\"min-h-[20px] flex flex-col items-start gap-3 whitespace-pre-wrap break-words overflow-x-auto\">\n<div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert light\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Children with ASD may exhibit the following traits:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Difficulty expressing emotions and thoughts<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Limited use of gestures for communication<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Challenges with maintaining eye contact<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">A tendency to obsess over a single conversational topic<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Differences in play behavior, including struggles with turn-taking and imaginative play<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Limited initiation or response in social interactions<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">In contrast, a child with ADHD might engage in nonstop talking, displaying a higher likelihood of interrupting others during conversations and attempting to dominate discussions. It&#8217;s essential to consider the subject matter, as some children with autism can talk extensively about topics of particular interest to them.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696482169899{padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<\/p>\n<div class=\"flex flex-grow flex-col gap-3 max-w-full\">\n<div class=\"min-h-[20px] flex flex-col items-start gap-3 whitespace-pre-wrap break-words overflow-x-auto\">\n<div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert light\">\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\"><strong>Children with ASD typically exhibit a preference for order and repetition.<\/strong> They often display a strong inclination toward maintaining consistency and adhering to established routines or ritualized patterns of both verbal and nonverbal behavior. For instance, they may repeatedly read the same book or insist on having identical meals for dinner every night. Any alterations to these routines can lead to distress and irritability.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">In contrast, a child with ADHD may not share this affinity for sameness, even if it could potentially benefit them. <strong>Children with ADHD tend to avoid engaging in the same activity repeatedly or for prolonged periods, preferring variety and change in their activities.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696481061336{padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text]<span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 32px; color: #404040;\"><strong>What Are The Signs of ADHD?<\/strong><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][vc_separator color=&#8221;custom&#8221; align=&#8221;align_left&#8221; border_width=&#8221;3&#8243; el_width=&#8221;10&#8243; accent_color=&#8221;#f3781e&#8221;][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-13081\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1341\" height=\"893\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1.png 1341w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1-1024x682.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1-768x511.png 768w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1-500x333.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1-800x533.png 800w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1-1280x852.png 1280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Inattentive-ADHD1-272x182.png 272w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1341px) 100vw, 1341px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696481823576{padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #404040; font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Predominantly Inattentive<br \/>\n<\/strong>Kids who are inattentive (easily distracted) have trouble focusing their attention, concentrating, and staying on task.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #f3781e;\">\r\n\t<a class=\"paoc-popup-click paoc-popup-cust-11662 paoc-popup-simple_link paoc-popup-link\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\">Main Signs of Inattentiveness<\/a>\r\n\r\n<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-13079 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"858\" height=\"572\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD1.png 858w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD1-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD1-768x512.png 768w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD1-500x333.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD1-800x533.png 800w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD1-272x182.png 272w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 858px) 100vw, 858px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696481836050{padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\"><strong>Predominantly Hyperactive\/Impulsive<br \/>\n<\/strong>Kids of this subtype feel restless and have trouble with impulsivity.\u00a0 Easily bored, they find it difficult to sit still for long periods (e.g., for a meal or while doing homework).\u00a0Smaller children may run, jump or climb constantly and invariably, have more accidents and injuries than others. Without meaning to, they may act in ways that disrupt others.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #f3781e;\">\r\n\t<a class=\"paoc-popup-click paoc-popup-cust-11660 paoc-popup-simple_link paoc-popup-link\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\">Main Signs of Hyperactivity &amp; Impulsiveness<\/a>\r\n\r\n<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-13080 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2.png 1340w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2-1024x682.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2-768x512.png 768w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2-500x333.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2-800x533.png 800w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2-1280x853.png 1280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Hyper-ADHD2-272x182.png 272w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696481083959{padding-right: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Combined<br \/>\n<\/strong>Symptoms of the inattentive and hyperactive\/impulsive sub types are equally present.\u00a0Because symptoms can change over time, the presentation may change over time as well.\u00a0<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; gap=&#8221;15&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696482359755{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text]<span style=\"color: #404040;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 22px; font-family: Antonio;\">Early Intervention<\/span><br \/>\n<\/strong><span style=\"font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Behavior therapy works best when it begins early in a child\u2019s life because younger children have simpler problems that may be responsive to ABA therapy.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">The elasticity of a younger child\u2019s brain is more amenable to intervention. As a result, the child\u2019s self-esteem remains intact, family dysfunction is reduced and the prognosis for school is much brighter.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-14980 alignleft ls-is-cached lazyloaded\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Picture110.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 239px) 100vw, 239px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Picture110.png 630w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Picture110-300x233.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Picture110-500x389.png 500w\" alt=\"\" width=\"239\" height=\"186\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Picture110.png 630w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Picture110-300x233.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Picture110-500x389.png 500w\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Picture110.png\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 239px) 100vw, 239px\" \/><span style=\"color: #404040;\"><strong>Children with ADHD often struggle in school and in the community due to a lack of help and from a misunderstanding of their condition.<\/strong>\u00a0This can lead to frustration, increasing inappropriate behavior, poor academic achievement, and eventually low self-esteem and depression.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #f3781e;\"><a style=\"color: #f3781e;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/early-intervention\/\">LEARN MORE ABOUT EARLY INTERVENTION<\/a><\/span><\/strong>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696524852586{padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"color: #404040;\"><span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 22px;\"><strong>Parent\/Family Coaching<br \/>\n<\/strong><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 17px;\">Parent and family coaching in ABA therapy for ADHD involves <strong>working to positively navigate through tantrums, defiance and tuning out parental instructions<\/strong> that can substantially improve lives, and the well-being of the family dynamic.<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-14982 alignright ls-is-cached lazyloaded\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Family-2a.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 277px) 100vw, 277px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Family-2a.png 740w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Family-2a-300x212.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Family-2a-500x353.png 500w\" alt=\"\" width=\"277\" height=\"196\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Family-2a.png 740w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Family-2a-300x212.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Family-2a-500x353.png 500w\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Family-2a.png\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 277px) 100vw, 277px\" \/><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 17px;\">It guides parents to interact differently with children and young adults in order to elicit desirable behavior and discourage disruptive ones. ABA therapy that focuses on coaching parents is recommended for young children with ADHD because young children are not mature enough to change their own behavior without their parents\u2019 help.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><strong>\u00a0<span style=\"color: #f3781e;\"><a style=\"color: #f3781e;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/parent-family-coaching\/\">LEARN MORE ABOUT PARENT &amp; FAMILY COACHING<\/a><\/span><\/strong>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696482370533{padding-top: 10px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696524870035{margin-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 40px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">The teenager years \u2013 notably one of the hardest periods in any life \u2013 establishes the benchmark of life finding a place between soaring passions and horrific despair.\u00a0 Stress. Grades. Acne Puberty. Socialization. Romance. All are just a few of the landmines on the way to the grand adult transition.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Young adults with ADHD often experience distractibility and poor concentration, made worse by the demands of school, intense socialization pressures, and hormonal changes of adolescence.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Some emotional consequences of ADHD include impulsive eating, irritability, meltdowns and angry outbursts, excessive use of electronics and video games for self-soothing, difficulty focusing due to exhaustion and fatigue, lack of motivation, uncooperative behavior with parents and siblings.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">We rely on establishing a strong collaborative relationship with parents for the best behavioral outcomes. Providing parents with effective tools and knowledge to provide can lead to increased self-confidence, hope in positive treatment outcomes, acceptance of challenges, and refining parenting skills to other children at home.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #f3781e;\"><a style=\"color: #f3781e;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/development-milestones-adolescent-years\/\">LEARN MORE ABOUT DEVELOPMENT MILESTONES &#8211; ADOLESCENT YEARS<\/a><\/span><\/strong>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696524924924{margin-right: -20px !important;margin-left: 20px !important;padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;background-color: #eee4ce !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Without treatment, ADHD can lead to poor grades, missed assignments and frequent moments of inattentiveness.\u00a0 As the teenager continues to mature, ADHD reenergizes itself with impulsiveness, immaturity and risk-taking\/thrill seeking which may lead to car accidents, heavy drinking,\u00a0<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-11600 alignright ls-is-cached lazyloaded\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 235px) 100vw, 235px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-120x120.png 120w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-384x384.png 384w\" alt=\"\" width=\"235\" height=\"235\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-120x120.png 120w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview-384x384.png 384w\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/Picture12-removebg-preview.png\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 235px) 100vw, 235px\" \/>and substance abuse.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #404040; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Often teens with ADHD work extra hard to maintain focus and use appropriate behavior at school and work, which can lead to emotional \u201cunloading\u201d and attention dysregulation when they are home.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696525068237{margin-top: -160px !important;padding